    "The R 2 represents the proportion of variance (in the target variable) that has been explained by the independent variables in the model and was calculated as:",
    "where ŷ i is the predicted value of the ith sample and y i is the corresponding true value for total n samples.",
    "Ȳ Represents the mean across all y.",
    "In this formulation, the R 2 is not interchangeable with the correlation coefficient squared.",
    "All predictions were performed using linear ridge regression as it showed a favourable ratio of computation time to accuracy in previous work 104 and preliminary testing (see Supplementary Fig. 21)."
